 # Changelog
 
+## 0.12.4
+
+- Fixed the real-browser `/posts/popular` mount failure: Popular pages created `PopularPageController.controller` but did not publish it as `App.pageController`, while the shared compact-layout engine unconditionally read `App.pageController.signal`.
+- Popular mounts now assign and explicitly pass their AbortSignal before connecting shared layout code.
+- Popular cleanup disconnects compact-layout observers and clears only its own shared page controller.
+- Hardened compact-layout connection against a missing or already-aborted signal so one failed mount cannot generate a repeating watchdog error loop.
+- Added focused v0.12.4 regression coverage; 60 executable tests now pass.
+
 ## 0.12.3
 
 - Fixed the current bare `/posts/popular` route by resolving **The Past 24 Hours** to the current UTC day and by deriving canonical dates from Pawchive's period links before falling back to today.
