-# Pawchive.pw Media Filter v0.12.2 specification
+# Pawchive.pw Media Filter v0.12.4 specification
+
+## v0.12.4 Popular mount-controller contract
+
+- The active Popular page `AbortController` must be assigned to both `PopularPageController.controller` and the shared `App.pageController` before any shared UI or compact-layout code is connected.
+- Shared compact-layout connection accepts an explicit AbortSignal and must never dereference `App.pageController.signal` without a null/aborted guard.
+- Popular cleanup disconnects compact-layout observers, aborts the controller, and clears `App.pageController` only when it still points to that same controller.
+- A failed Popular mount must not enter a watchdog loop that repeatedly throws `Cannot read properties of null (reading 'signal')`.
 
